node.text:
You can care about someone without taking responsibility for their well being.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
You may want or need to be in a caretaker role in some relationships in your life (for a child, a person with a disability, an incapacitated loved one, etc.).⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
There may be other instances in which you care deeply, but it is not appropriate or desired for you to assume the caretaker role. When you take on this role when it is not wanted or needed, or when it is damaging to your own emotional health, it can cause major problems in the relationship.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Ask yourself, is it my role to caretake in this context? If not, how can I express care without caretaking? ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
